## Use Case 14 - Making a balcony/garden/outdoor area more pollinator-friendly (Aye)

**Goal:** Someone who participated in an online questionnaire/study was intrigued by the information provided in the study and wanted to know whether they could make their own balcony/garden/outdoor area more pollinator-friendly.

**Actors:** 1) someone from Germany, 2) the researcher of the study, 3) plant stores, 4) friends and family

**Resources:** information provided by researchers, the internet, garden center websites (shopping), EuroAPPA, shops/nurseries

**Steps:** 

1) A participant finished a questionnaire about pollinator-friendly practices

2) They realized that their balcony is still empty 

3) They ponder whether it is possible to make a pollinator-friendly refuge using the limited space (would it even help), while also getting some benefits (e.g., spices, veggies) 

4:

a) Look up on the internet about pollinator-friendly balconies 

b) Contacts the researcher to ask for more specific suggestions 

5:

a) The researcher sends a list of plants that could work for the intended purpose of the participant (also information about the planting season, etc.) 

