## Use Case 18 – A business wants to improve its corporate sustainability (Tom Breeze, VALOR project)

  
 **Goal**: The business wants to know which of its supplying growers is most at risk from pollinator decline and what the most effective solutions that they can support the grower to undertake are.

**Resources**: Models to evaluating local plant-pollinator network diversity and resilience over time.

**Actors**: The business’ sustainability team, growers and intermediaries (e.g. co-operatives)

**Steps**: 

1. The business identifies the location of farms in it’s supply chains on maps
2. Using the Butterfly 5.2 and 5.3 tools, they draw polygons around the farms and select “crop pollination” targeting the key crops to get recommendations.
3. They use a network analysis model (maybe something that can be built into the tools) to explore the network diversity of each farm, flagging those which have very low expected diversity.
4. They use the recommendations from step 2 to target investment in pollinator conservation
5. They repeat the process each year, exploring how their investments have improved the diversity of networks, with intermittent monitoring to confirm their projections.
6. They can then report this as part of their corporate sustainability requirements

